  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 486f137ac72fd004c9131b1648f76380, type: 3}
  m_Name: Deltoid_muscle.L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Deltoid_muscle.L
  partName: Deltoid muscle Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left deltoid muscle is located over the lateral aspect of the canine shoulder
    joint and consists of multiple portions working together to control forelimb
    movement. Originating from the scapular spine and acromion, it inserts onto the
    humerus and primarily functions to flex the shoulder joint.
  - The muscle also assists with stabilizing the shoulder during locomotion and weight-bearing
    activities. Its coordinated contractions contribute to smooth limb advancement,
    turning, and controlled positioning of the forelimb during movement. The deltoid
    works alongside surrounding shoulder muscles to maintain joint integrity and
    flexibility.
